trend_summary: 2000-2020 imagery shows gradual suburban infill: new cul-de-sac subdivisions, small commercial pads and wider roads replace pockets of forest and farmland, yet large green tracts and a golf course persist. Built area expands mainly west and southeast while central woodland shrinks. Overall pattern remains leafy, automobile-oriented housing.
notable_changes: West side farmland cleared and replaced by a curvilinear housing subdivision.
Southeastern corner gains several residential blocks and a connector road.
Central forest corridor narrowed by scattered lot development and driveway extensions.
